{"type":"message","id":"c113d097","parentId":"87f6691f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:29:35.676Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rdqfq76dwqeb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142909\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n- CFI Compression Experiment completed - found that pure CFI thresholds are too aggressive\r\n- Key insight: Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter combining CFI and frequency\r\n- Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step is to run the pending experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\n1. I need to implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. The formula is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n3. This should distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nTo run this experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Create or modify a script that computes the hybrid score\r\n2. Run it on the pulse corpus\r\n3. Compare results against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nBut wait - I'm stateless and each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. The pulse script takes about 35 seconds to run. Let me think about what concrete file edit I can make.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\" - this is the most concrete next step\r\n- I should create a script to run this experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Computes CFI and frequency for each token\r\n3. Applies the hybrid scoring formula\r\n4. Compares against binary thresholds\r\n5. Outputs results\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at what already exists. Let me check if there's an existing experiment script I can modify.\r\n\r\nFrom the notes:\r\n- \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\" - this is the synthesis from the experiment\r\n- There should be experiment data somewhere\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a precise Python script to validate the hybrid scoring approach, focusing on implementing the scoring formula and generating comparative metrics.\r\n\r\nI'll start by defining the core scoring function, ensuring it captures the nuanced filtering mechanism we've identified. The script will systematically process the pulse corpus, applying both hybrid and binary threshold strategies to provide a clear performance comparison.\r\n\r\nThe implementation will involve careful data preprocessing, score calculation, and result analysis to demonstrate the effectiveness of the three-dimensional filtering approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment identified that pure CFI thresholds are too aggressive (losing 92.9% recall). The next step is clearly defined: implement and run the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring formula to test if it distinguishes constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) using the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)^0.5 / 10). This will test whether hybrid scoring outperforms binary thresholds at distinguishing metaprogramming artifacts from true research tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI × Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n================================================\r\nFormula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)^0.5 / 10)\r\n\r\nHypothesis: This distinguishes:\r\n- \"constant format\" tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (high but meaningless)\r\n- \"research trajectory\" tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → score ∈ (0.25, 0.87] (contextually meaningful)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses(pulse_dir: str = \"state/pulses\"):\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse files.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    pulse_dir = Path(pulse_dir)\r\n    for pf in sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        try:\r\n            content = pf.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\"file\": pf.name, \"content\": content, \"tokens\": content.split()})\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            print(f\"Error loading {pf}: {e}\")\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef compute_token_metrics(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute CFI and frequency for each token.\"\"\"\r\n    token_positions = Counter()\r\n    token_occurrences = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        seen_in_pulse = set()\r\n        for token in pulse[\"tokens\"]:\r\n            if token not in seen_in_pulse:\r\n                token_positions[token] += 1\r\n                seen_in_pulse.add(token)\r\n            token_occurrences[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    n_pulses = len(pulses)\r\n    metrics = {}\r\n    for token, positions in token_positions.items():\r\n        cfi = positions / n_pulses\r\n        freq = token_occurrences[token]\r\n        score = cfi * min(1.0, math.sqrt(freq) / 10.0)\r\n        metrics[token] = {\"cfi\": cfi, \"freq\": freq, \"score\": score}\r\n    \r\n    return metrics, n_pulses\r\n\r\ndef analyze_hybrid_filter(metrics, score_threshold=0.1):\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze hybrid filter performance.\"\"\"\r\n    results = {\"kept\": [], \"removed\": [], \"stats\": {}}\r\n    \r\n    for token, m in metrics.items():\r\n        entry = {\"token\": token, \"cfi\": m[\"cfi\"], \"freq\": m[\"freq\"], \"score\": m[\"score\"]}\r\n        if m[\"score\"] >= score_threshold:\r\n            results[\"kept\"].append(entry)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:29:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376975674}}
{"type":"message","id":"5824b182","parentId":"c113d097","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:29:35.679Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rdqfq76dwqeb_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI × Freq Scoring Experiment\n================================================\nFormula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)^0.5 / 10)\n\nHypothesis: This distinguishes:\n- \"constant format\" tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (high but meaningless)\n- \"research trajectory\" tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → score ∈ (0.25, 0.87] (contextually meaningful)\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport math\nfrom collections import Counter\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef load_pulses(pulse_dir: str = \"state/pulses\"):\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse files.\"\"\"\n    pulses = []\n    pulse_dir = Path(pulse_dir)\n    for pf in sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\n        try:\n            content = pf.read_text()\n            pulses.append({\"file\": pf.name, \"content\": content, \"tokens\": content.split()})\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error loading {pf}: {e}\")\n    return pulses\n\ndef compute_token_metrics(pulses):\n    \"\"\"Compute CFI and frequency for each token.\"\"\"\n    token_positions = Counter()\n    token_occurrences = Counter()\n    \n    for pulse in pulses:\n        seen_in_pulse = set()\n        for token in pulse[\"tokens\"]:\n            if token not in seen_in_pulse:\n                token_positions[token] += 1\n                seen_in_pulse.add(token)\n            token_occurrences[token] += 1\n    \n    n_pulses = len(pulses)\n    metrics = {}\n    for token, positions in token_positions.items():\n        cfi = positions / n_pulses\n        freq = token_occurrences[token]\n        score = cfi * min(1.0, math.sqrt(freq) / 10.0)\n        metrics[token] = {\"cfi\": cfi, \"freq\": freq, \"score\": score}\n    \n    return metrics, n_pulses\n\ndef analyze_hybrid_filter(metrics, score_threshold=0.1):\n    \"\"\"Analyze hybrid filter performance.\"\"\"\n    results = {\"kept\": [], \"removed\": [], \"stats\": {}}\n    \n    for token, m in metrics.items():\n        entry = {\"token\": token, \"cfi\": m[\"cfi\"], \"freq\": m[\"freq\"], \"score\": m[\"score\"]}\n        if m[\"score\"] >= score_threshold:\n            results[\"kept\"].append(entry)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376975677}}
{"type":"message","id":"41fa2bce","parentId":"5824b182","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:29:44.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed. Let me now summarize what happened.\n\nThe pulse created a new mutation for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). The mutation is a Python script implementing the experiment. The script:\n\n1. Loads pulse files\n2. Computes CFI and frequency for each token\n3. Applies hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)^0.5 / 10)\n4. Analyzes the filter performance\n\nThe key commit shows:\n- 6 files changed, 284 insertions(+), 107 deletions(-)\n- Created: memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 142909.md and mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 142909.mutation\n- Renamed previous mutation to rejected\n\nLet me give a concise summary.","thinkingSignature":"829b25c9dada5ac96eca749c9e1454985f8a40c92ca5b607011ca4f43ca7656b"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 14:29**\n\n**Cycle:** 2026-03-24 142909 | Duration: ~35s\n\n**What happened:**\n- The CFI Compression Experiment's prior run identified that pure CFI thresholds are too aggressive — losing 92.9% recall on research trajectory tokens\n- The agent synthesized the key insight: need a **three-dimensional filter** combining CFI + frequency to distinguish metaprogramming artifacts from true research tokens\n- **New mutation proposed:** `experiments/hybrid_cfi_freq_experiment.py` — implements **Strategy C** using the formula:\n  > `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)^0.5 / 10)`\n  - Intended to push constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) toward score ~1.0 (recognizable as artificial)\n  - While keeping research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) in the 0.25–0.87 range\n\n**Mutations:** 1 proposed, 1 rejected (the prior pure-CFI experiment)\n\n**Status:** 🟡 Next instantiation needs to execute the proposed Python experiment and compare hybrid scoring against binary thresholds on the 200-pulse corpus."}]